stunner_listener_connections_active(<node, namespace, pod>, name=<listener_name>)
stunner_listener_packets_total(<node, namespace, pod>, name=<listener_name>, direction=rx,tx)




The recommended way to install Jitsi into Kubernetes is deploying the media servers into the host-network namespace of the Kubernetes nodes (hostNetwork: true), or using a NodePort service or a dedicated Ingress to ingest WebRTC media traffic into the network. However, these options allows only one JVB per Kubernetes node and the host-network deployment model also comes with a set of uncanny operational limitations and security concerns. 
